From: m5-linux project
Subject: [PATCH 1/N] soc: Add M4 Pro/Max and M5 SoC identifiers

Add T6040 (M4 Pro), T6041 (M4 Max), T8142 (M5), T6050 (M5 Pro), and
T6051 (M5 Max) to the SoC identifier table and TARGET dispatch chain.

EARLY_UART_BASE values verified from the `uart0` ADT node `reg`, translated
through each board's `arm-io` `ranges`, in UniversalMac_26.5_25F71_Restore.ipsw.
Method calibrated against upstream T8132 (J604 reg 0x1ad200000 -> 0x3ad200000):

  T6040 (M4 Pro)  : 0x429200000  (boards J616s, J773s, J614s)
  T6041 (M4 Max)  : 0x429200000  (boards J616c, J575c, J614c — same as M4 Pro)
  T8142 (M5 base) : 0x3a5200000  (boards J704/J813/J815; arm-io base 0x2_10000000)
  T6050 (M5 Pro)  : 0x505200000  (boards J716s/J716c/J714s/J714c)
  T6051 (M5 Max)  : UNKNOWN — t6051 is absent from 25F71 (no dtree/kernelcache)

NOTE: m1n1 uses EARLY_UART_BASE (not UART_BASE), and the per-TARGET block in
soc.h defines only that macro. MAX_CPUS lives in smp.h as a single global (24);
it is NOT a per-SoC soc.h field, so it is intentionally omitted here. M5 Pro/Max
enumerate >24 cpu nodes in the ADT, so smp.h MAX_CPUS likely needs bumping
during bring-up (separate change).

--- a/src/soc.h
+++ b/src/soc.h
@@ -30,6 +30,11 @@
 #define T6030 0x6030
 #define T6031 0x6031
 #define T6034 0x6034
+/* M4 Pro/Max */
+#define T6040 0x6040
+#define T6041 0x6041
+/* M5 Pro/Max */
+#define T6050 0x6050
+#define T6051 0x6051
+/* M5 base */
+#define T8142 0x8142

 #if TARGET == T8103
 #define EARLY_UART_BASE 0x235200000
@@ ... (after the existing TARGET == T6030 / T6031 / T8132 entries) ...
+#elif TARGET == T6040 || TARGET == T6041
+/* M4 Pro/Max — verified from j616s/j616c ADT (arm-io base 0x2_00000000) */
+#define EARLY_UART_BASE 0x429200000
+#elif TARGET == T8142
+/* M5 base — verified from j704 ADT (arm-io base 0x2_10000000) */
+#define EARLY_UART_BASE 0x3a5200000
+#elif TARGET == T6050
+/* M5 Pro — verified from j716s/j716c/j714s ADT (arm-io base 0x2_00000000) */
+#define EARLY_UART_BASE 0x505200000
+#elif TARGET == T6051
+/* M5 Max — XXX: t6051 absent from 25F71, EARLY_UART_BASE unconfirmed */
+#define EARLY_UART_BASE 0xXXXXXXXXX
